- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the proposed framework in autonomous driving vehicles, which is a common topic in robotics research.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the proposed framework is based on a deep neural network for semantic segmentation, which is a common topic in machine learning research.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper proposes a framework that uses AI techniques to improve the performance of real-time scene parsing for autonomous driving vehicles.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of multiple cameras for scene parsing, which is a common topic in multimedia research.
